duties:
The duties of this position include:
•	provide one-on-one or group support to students in introductory and intermediate French courses
•	helping beginning and intermediate students practice their French pronunciation, develop their speaking skills, understand essential grammatical concepts and improve their vocabulary;
•	guiding informal conversations in French to help intermediate students improve their spontaneous interactions in French;
•	reviewing material learned in class and helping students with questions about grammar and syntax;
•	helping coordinate events, such as movie nights, conversation workshops, cultural activities, etc.

The TA duties will consist of:
- Supervising six weeks of ANSYS labs, 6 hours per week;
- Grading six lab reports for a class of approximately 80 students (some reports will be done in groups), providing very detailed feedback;
- Holding weekly office hours for six weeks;
- Invigilating quizzes and midterm;
- Meeting with the course instructor.

qualifications_minimum:
The candidate must preferably have:
- Knowledge of Finite Element Methods;
- Experience with ANSYS;
- Previous experience with grading work.

